environment but always the meaning of Poe's words. Because these works are shaped by a single imagination and because they are experienced in time, as a process, each work has its own "way of going." The aim of the interpretation is to find this way and go along with it; to live each work dynamically, as it "happens," while tracing its interaction with other works.Originally published in 1973.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFantasy literature, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aFantasy literature, American. 0aPhenomenology and literaturexHistoryy19th century. 0aPhenomenology and literature. 0aPoe, Edgar Allan, 1809-1849xCriticism and interpretation. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979z978311042684708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Literaturez978311041353308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140087304340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400873043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400873043.jpg  a978-3-11-041353-3  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Literature  a978-3-11-042684-7  Princet